<div id="review_1612692416" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1612692416" />
    <a title="Nina Arce" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35338804-nina-arce"><img alt="Nina Arce" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1497632055p2/35338804.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1612692416?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nina Arce" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nina Arce" href="/user/show/35338804-nina-arce">Nina Arce</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35338804-nina-arce?shelf=writing-books">writing-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35338804-nina-arce?shelf=bought-2016">bought-2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35338804-nina-arce?shelf=writing-books-reviewed">writing-books-reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35338804-nina-arce?shelf=read-2016">read-2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/35338804-nina-arce?shelf=have-as-audio">have-as-audio</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1612692416" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5515392453947443149">This may very well be the most horridly pretentious writing book I&apos;ve ever seen. The only thing stopping me from throwing it across the room in sheer despair was that I bought the audiobook version - and there was enough pain involved in actually listening that it would have been almost vulgar to add that of broken glass.<br/><br/>Seriously, though: ugh. There are some good points in this, certainly, but they&apos;re drowning in the haughtiest filler possible. My main problem is not the highly literary angle p</span>
  <span id="freeText5515392453947443149" style="display:none">This may very well be the most horridly pretentious writing book I've ever seen. The only thing stopping me from throwing it across the room in sheer despair was that I bought the audiobook version - and there was enough pain involved in actually listening that it would have been almost vulgar to add that of broken glass.<br /><br />Seriously, though: ugh. There are some good points in this, certainly, but they're drowning in the haughtiest filler possible. My main problem is not the highly literary angle per se - that part is understandable, given that Prose has taught creative writing at graduate level. Although I wasn't familiar with all of the authors she quoted, I felt I knew enough of them to be able to follow along and see her points. But honestly? I know I can come off as a bit arrogant myself at times, so you'd think I'd be obliged to have a higher than average tolerance level for this sort of thing - and I believe I do. This, however, went above and beyond. It was utter misery.<br /><br />The only reason I'm giving it two (and not just one) stars is the fact that despite it all, I did take two or three tangible pieces of actual advice away from it. If anyone reading this is considering getting this title, though: please get the written version, and please skim as quickly as you possibly can. I wouldn't want any of my friends or followers to suffer the way I did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5515392453947443149" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


